This paper discusses the design of artificial immune systems (AISs), which are a type of artificial intelligence system. The paper proposes that AISs should be made more biologically realistic by drawing inspiration from organisms with innate immune systems and employing systemic models of the immune system. This suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper discusses contemporary research that could be impacted by more biologically-realistic AISs, which could also place it under cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.RO (Robotics).
